						<img alt='' src='https://0.gravatar.com/avatar/f344836fdac4ec0270a54b159773c29e?s=42&#038;d=identicon&#038;r=G' class='avatar avatar-42' height='42' width='42' />						<b class="fn">alicorn</b> <span class="says">says:</span>					</div><!-- .comment-author -->

					<div class="comment-metadata">
						<a href="https://carcinisation.com/2015/04/03/have-mercy/#comment-2422">
							<time datetime="2015-04-17T17:30:38-08:00">
								April 17, 2015 at 5:30 PM							</time>
						</a>
											</div><!-- .comment-metadata -->

									</footer><!-- .comment-meta -->

				<div class="comment-content">
					<p>I don&#8217;t support arbitrary parental choice, and even if we assume you can engineer in obedience reliably (which seems non-obvious), I would not want it to be deployed because it would make kids easy to abuse (whereas most of the tweaks I&#8217;d support seem like they&#8217;d make kids less <em>appealing</em> to abuse, even if they don&#8217;t directly affect parental ability).</p>
<p id="comment-like-2422" data-liked=comment-not-liked class="comment-likes comment-not-liked"><a href="https://carcinisation.com/2015/04/03/have-mercy/?like_comment=2422&#038;_wpnonce=bd946e57a3" class="comment-like-link needs-login" rel="nofollow" data-blog="71183487"><span>Like</span></a><span id="comment-like-count-2422" class="comment-like-feedback">Like</span></p>
				</div><!-- .comment-content -->

				<div class="reply"><a rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='/2015/04/03/have-mercy/?like_comment=2382&#038;_wpnonce=a3319f12cf&#038;replytocom=2422#respond' data-commentid="2422" data-postid="447" data-belowelement="div-comment-2422" data-respondelement="respond" aria-label='Reply to alicorn'>Reply</a></div>			</article><!-- .comment-body -->
