				<div class="comment-content">
					<p>Not to nitpick, but: &#8220;babies who will need to learn to roll instead of walk,&#8221; came off as a very odd sentence to me. I had to struggle to interpret what you meant; was it a baby that never learns to walk?</p>
<p>All babies learn to roll before learning to walk, so it&#8217;s not an &#8220;instead of&#8221; proposition. Maybe &#8220;Babies who learn to roll but never learn to walk&#8221; would be better?</p>
